      "side": 1,
      "message": "I see. Looking at the canonical example for exec.Command: https://golang.org/pkg/os/exec/#Command\n\nIt would be cleaner to write:\n\ncmd.Env \u003d append(os.Environ(),\n        \"GOPATH\u003d\" + strings.Join([]string{cfg.TestWorkspace, cfg.CommonWorkspace, cfg.SysGopath}, \":\"),\n        \"GOBIN\u003d\" + outDir,\n)\n\nThose two look like the only two variables you need to override, with everything else coming from the environment.",
