      "writtenOn": "2018-04-26T20:59:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s \u0027sudo\u0027 which does that, not portage. e.g.\n$ sudo emerge .../...\nsudo will clear the environment, so if you want to set USE flags,\n\nthis doesn\u0027t work:\n$ USE\u003dgold sudo emerge .../...\n\nbut this does:\n$ sudo USE\u003dgold emerge .../...\n\nNote that our wrappers for the boards (e.g. emerge-chell), specifically invoke sudo with \"sudo -E\" so it preserves the environment. It makes \"USE\u003dgold emerge-chell .../...\" work.",
      "parentUuid": "65b2c6d6_63121160",
